    "d9e91537-6225-4b57-bd84-e5d10e8558b3": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "item_ELCYMT": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What makes a rubber or silicone broom better than a regular broom?",
            "content": "<p>Rubber and silicone brooms use flexible, anti-static bristles that attract dust, hair and debris rather than just pushing it around. This makes them far more effective than traditional brooms, especially for pet hair and fine particles.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_DLntwV": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": " Should I wash my broom?",
            "content": "<p>For regular brooms, it is not recommended to wash the bristle because it destroys the hairs. But rubber broom and silicone brooms can easily be washed with water, detergents and even bleach to keep them hygienic.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_nkCiz9": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": " Can you mop with a broom?",
            "content": "<p>You absolutely can! You can pair our brooms with our Quick Mop Floor Wipes or Quick Mop Microfibre Floor Cloths, transforming your broom into a mop. Even without the Wipes, you can use the broom bristles to scrub dirt with water on floors, walls or any surface.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_gbaLKR": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": " When should I get a new broom?",
            "content": "<p>Unlike traditional brooms, which often need replacing every few months as dust, hair and dirt become trapped in the bristles, a natural rubber (silicone) broom is built to last for years.</p><p>Its durable, anti-stick bristles won't lose their shape, resist the build-up of hair and debris, and can simply be rinsed clean with warm water. Strong, long-lasting and easy to maintain, it's a smarter alternative to a regular broom.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_ATRXDy": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the best broom for wooden floors?",
            "content": "<p>Both silicone and natural rubber brooms are an excellent choice for wooden floors. Their bristles naturally generate static electricity, making it easy to attract and collect dust, hair and fine debris without scratching your floors.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_ikMTTN": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why are our brooms so effective for picking up pet hair?",
            "content": "<p>Fitted with dense, flexible anti-static bristles that attract and lift pet hair from hard floors and carpets with ease, making it quick and effortless to collect even stubborn hair that vacuums often miss.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_JiUKf8": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": " What to look for in a broom?",
            "content": "<p>When choosing a new broom, look for durability, high-quality materials, and a design that’s easy to keep clean after use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_BX64wX": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": " How do you get pet hair out of carpet without a vacuum?",
            "content": "<p>A rubber or silicone bristle broom is one of the most effective tools for removing stubborn pet hair from carpets, lifting embedded hair with ease—often outperforming a vacuum cleaner.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_QhLHeQ": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I use a rubber broom on all floor types?",
            "content": "<p>Yes, you absolutely can! Rubber and silicone brooms are safe to use on all floor types including tiles, timber, laminate, concrete, vinyl and sealed floors. They’re gentle enough not to scratch while still being highly effective at cleaning.</p>"
          }
        },
        "template--19202935587090__d9e91537-6225-4b57-bd84-e5d10e8558b3-1686662624baccc985-0": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I clean the broom after use?",
            "content": "<p>Simply rinse the broom under warm water to remove dust, hair and debris. The anti-stick bristles are designed to release dirt easily, helping the broom stay clean and hygienic with minimal effort.</p>"
          }
        },
        "template--19202935587090__d9e91537-6225-4b57-bd84-e5d10e8558b3-1686662624baccc985-1": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How long does a rubber or silicone broom last?",
            "content": "<p>With proper care, rubber and silicone brooms are highly durable and can last for years. Unlike traditional brooms, the bristles don’t splay or lose shape quickly, making them a long-term cleaning solution.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_PYNEUa": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the difference between the rubber and silicone brooms?",
            "content": "<p>Not all that much - some would say that  rubber is a bit firmer for tougher cleaning, while silicone is somewhat softer for lighter, everyday<strong> </strong>use. Both are highly durable, easy to clean with water, and far more effective than traditional brooms for picking up hair and fine particles.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_aTBcVY": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the most ideal broom for small spaces such as caravans / tiny homes / bathrooms?",
            "content": "<p>Our Japanese Silicone Broom with swivel head. It has a narrow 30cm head and swivels to get around tight spots with ease.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_XdrFyG": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Where is our warehouse located?",
            "content": "<p>Our warehouse is located in Cheltenham, Melbourne. </p>"
          }
        },
        "template--19202935587090__d9e91537-6225-4b57-bd84-e5d10e8558b3-1686662624baccc985-2": {
          "type": "item",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do BrightTools Squeegees come with a warranty?",
            "content": "<p>Absolutely! We stand behind the quality of our squeegees. Each one is backed by a 2 year <a href=\"/pages/warranty\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Warranty\">warranty</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "dc709b98-8f74-4f10-9911-a3d0da4bdcf4": {
          "type": "item",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "I have a question that is not listed here. How can I get in touch with BrightTools?",
            "content": "<p>No problem at all! We're here to help. If you have any additional questions or need further assistance, simply visit our <a href=\"/pages/contact\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Contact\">contact page.</a></p>"
          }
        }
      },
